Disclosing the company’s operating results and performance in its just concluded financial year which ended December 31, 2017, Chairman, Dr. Elijah Akpan noted that deliberate steps are being taken towards ensuring the company’s long term growth.
  
Akpan, said this at the company’s 42nd yearly general meeting (AGM) in Lagos at the weekend, that it recorded significant improvement in its results as revenue increased to N4.8 billion, compared to N3.9 billion recorded in the corresponding period of last year), while operating profit dropped from N618 million to N595 million.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .